# Conventional Commits

When creating or suggesting git commits in this repository, use [Conventional Commits 1.0.0](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/).

Format:

```
<type>[optional scope]: <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]
```

- **feat:** new feature (MINOR in SemVer)
- **fix:** bug fix (PATCH)
- **docs:** documentation only
- **chore:** maintenance (deps, tooling) with no production code change
- **test:** tests only
- **refactor:** code change that is neither a fix nor a feature
- **build** / **ci:** build system or CI changes

Use lowercase types. Keep the subject line imperative and under ~72 characters. Add a body when context is needed.

Breaking changes: append `!` after type/scope (`feat(api)!: ...`) or add a `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer.

Examples:

```
feat(cli): add init-board command
fix(board): release lock when script exits non-zero
docs: document conventional commit messages
chore: add deno.lock
```

Do not commit unless the user explicitly asks. When they do, follow this format.
